\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
With the same 
\begin_inset Formula ${\cal F}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $M$
\end_inset

 as above.
 Suppose 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi=q\varphi^{u}$
\end_inset

 is a scalar multiple of the geometric potential.
 Then, for 
\begin_inset Formula $q\in(-\infty,1)$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\vphi$
\end_inset

 has a unique equilibrium state 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu_{q}$
\end_inset

 which is, fully supported, 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu_{\varphi}({\rm Reg})=1$
\end_inset

, Bernoulli, and is the weak
\begin_inset Formula $^{*}$
\end_inset

 limit of the weighted regular periodic orbits.
 Furthermore, the map 
\begin_inset Formula $q\mapsto P(q\vphi^{u})$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula $C^{1}$
\end_inset

 for 
\begin_inset Formula $q\in(-\infty,1)$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

