\begin_layout Remark
Both Eschenburg 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
cite{Eschenburg:1977kn}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 and Pesin 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
cite{Pesin:1977vi}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 proved that the stable foliation 
\begin_inset Formula $E^{s}$
\end_inset

 and unstable foliation 
\begin_inset Formula $E^{u}$
\end_inset

 are given by the stable and unstable Jacobi fields (as in Eberlein 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Eberlein:1973hu"

\end_inset

).
 In both work recalled above, they also showed when 
\begin_inset Formula $M$
\end_inset

 has no focal points then 
\begin_inset Formula $W^{s}(v)$
\end_inset

 (resp.
 
\begin_inset Formula $W^{u}(v)$
\end_inset

) is indeed the stable (resp.
 unstable) horoshpere on 
\begin_inset Formula $T^{1}M$
\end_inset

.
 More precisely, 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\widetilde{W^{s}}(v)=\{(x,-\nabla_{x}b_{v}^{+}):\ x\in H^{s}(v)\}\ {\rm and\ }\widetilde{W^{u}}(v)=\{(x,-\nabla_{x}b_{-v}):\ x\in H^{u}(v)\}.
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout --Separator--

\end_layout

\begin_layout --Separator--

\end_layout

