\begin_layout Definition
For 
\begin_inset Formula $v\in T^{1}M$
\end_inset

, let 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda^{u}(v)$
\end_inset

 be minimum eigenvalue of 
\begin_inset Formula ${\cal U}^{u}(v)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda^{s}(v)=\lambda^{u}(-v)$
\end_inset

.
 We define 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda(v)=\min(\lambda^{u}(v),\lambda^{s}(v)).$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout --Separator--

\end_layout

\begin_layout --Separator--

\end_layout

\begin_layout --Separator--

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let 
\begin_inset Formula $\Lambda$
\end_inset

 be the maximum eigenvalue of 
\begin_inset Formula ${\cal U}^{u}(v)$
\end_inset

 for 
\begin_inset Formula $v\in T^{1}M$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout --Separator--

\end_layout

\begin_layout --Separator--

\end_layout

\begin_layout --Separator--

\end_layout

\begin_layout --Separator--

